Chelsea manager, Thomas Tuchel, has named his side’s squad to face Real Madrid in the Champions League semi-final first-leg tie in Spain on Tuesday night. Tuchel named a 24-man squad to tackle Real Madrid at the Alfredo Di Stéfano Stadium in a post via Chelsea’s official website. Chelsea had knocked Porto out of the Champions League quarter-final stages, while Real Madrid eliminated Liverpool from the competition. The Blues head to the game after defeating West Ham United 1-0 in the Premier League last weekend, while Zinedine Zidane’s side played a 0-0 draw with Real Betis in the LaLiga. Below is Chelsea’s squad against Real Madrid;
Kepa Arrizabalaga, Antonio Rudiger, Marcos Alonso, Andreas Christensen, Jorginho, Thiago Silva, N’Golo Kante, Tammy Abraham, Christian Pulisic, Timo Werner, Willy Caballero, Kurt Zouma, Edouard Mendy, Olivier Giroud, Mason Mount, Callum Hudson-Odoi, Ben Chilwell, Hakim Ziyech, Billy Gilmour, Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Kai Havertz, Emerson Palmieri, Tino Anjorin. The kick-off time for Real Madrid vs Chelsea is 8 pm.